    "recap_headline": "Kent State University",
    "recap_text": "HARTFORD, Conn.\n\u2014 The Kent State Golden Flashes put together one of their most complete offensive performances of the season on Friday, pouring it on late to defeat Massachusetts 14-3 in eight innings at Murren Family Field at DiBenedetto Stadium. The win improved the Flashes to 16-4 overall and 6-1 in MAC play.\nKent State struck first in the top of the first inning when\nBrody Williams\nsingled to center to plate\nKolton Schaller\n, but the Minutemen answered with single runs in the second, third, and fourth innings to take a 3-1 lead. Massachusetts got two of its runs from the same player, Braden Sullivan, who accounted for a triple in the second, a solo home run in the fourth, and scored each time.\nCiaran Caughey\nsettled in after the early trouble, ultimately going six innings and striking out eight before turning things over to the bullpen.\nThe Flashes began chipping away in the sixth when\nBrady Marshall\ndoubled and eventually scored alongside\nMax Humphrey\non a fielding error by the UMass second baseman to pull within one at 3-2. Kent State then took the lead for good in the seventh, stringing together five consecutive singles to open the inning.\nMicah Rienstra-Kiracofe\n, entering as a pinch hitter, singled up the middle to score\nNolan Belcher\n, and Marshall followed with a bunt RBI single to score Williams. After\nLuke Matthews\nloaded the bases,\nRipken Reese\ncapped the frame with a sacrifice fly to make it 5-3 heading to the eighth.\nThe Flashes then put the game completely out of reach at the top of the eighth with an eight-run explosion. With the bases loaded and two walks already forcing in a run, Matthews delivered a two-run single to left center.\nMax Humphrey\nfollowed with a sacrifice fly, and Reese doubled to right center to plate Matthews. Then pinch hitter\nHunter Klotz\nstepped to the plate with Reese on third and\nSawyer Solitaria\non second and launched a three-run home run to deep right field to cap the inning and put the Flashes ahead 14-3.\nMarshall had a monster afternoon, going 3-for-4 with two doubles and two RBI. Matthews finished 2-for-5 with two RBI and two stolen bases. The Flashes stole nine bases on the day.\nGavin Jones\nearned the win in relief, tossing two scoreless innings to improve to 1-1 on the season.\nThe Flashes and Minutemen will play game two on\u00a0Saturday, March 21, at 1 p.m. ET.\n---\nBe The Difference, Support the Baseball Excellence Fund\nSupport the baseball program today by donating to the Baseball Excellence Fund by\nclicking here.\nFollow Kent State Baseball\nFor complete coverage of Kent State Baseball, download the official Kent State Golden Flashes app (\niOS\n,\nAndroid\n) and follow the Golden Flashes on social media on\nX\n,\nInstagram\n, and\nFacebook\nfor news and updates.",
